The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, May 30 (PTI): A junior Jet Airways pilot has been arrested for allegedly raping an air-hostess several times since May 2009 on the false promise of marrying her. Varun Agarwal was today remanded in police custody till June 5.          
	The police sought his custody on the ground that the investigation was on and medical reports of the accused and the alleged victim were awaited.                  
	 Shanghai (PTI): A statue of Rabindranath Tagore has been unveil-ed here by President Pratibha Patil, commemorating his journey to Shanghai that left a lasting impression on Chinese poets and writers. On the last leg of her six-day China visit, Patil unveiled the 125kg structure sculpted by Gautam Pal and paid floral tributes to the poet.                  
	 Tirupati (PTI): Anil Ambani rested in the guesthouse owned by elder brother Mukesh Ambanis company, RIL, at Tirumala on his way to the Lord Venkateswara temple on Saturday night. Anils group had scrapped a non-compete agreement with RIL last week in a sign of the brothers intention to buy peace.                  
	 Shivpuri (PTI): A 44-year-old jawan of the Madhya Pradesh Special Armed Force died of a heat stroke here on Sunday, officials said. Kedar Prasad Manjhi had suffered a heat stroke on May 28 and was rushed to the district hospital. This was the third death within a week in the district from heat stroke.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The National Capital Region will have four new passport seva kendras by March next year. The filing of passport applications will become easier and one will be out of the facility within 45 minutes of entering it, officials said.                  
	Ghaziabad (PTI): A 62-year-old man was hacked to death allegedly by his son after a fight over money, police said. The son has been arrested and sent to 14 days judicial custody.                                                                                                                                              
